desc: If you play this card in round 3/6/9/12, you immediately get 3/4/5/6 <FOOD>.

name: Bartering Hut
desc: Up to two times: Immediately spend any 2/3/4 building resources for 1 <SHEEP>/<PIG>/<CATTLE> from the general supply.

name: Wood Harvester
desc: In the field phase of each harvest, you get 1 <WOOD>/1 <FOOD> for each wood accumulation space with exactly 2 <WOOD>/at least 3 <WOOD>.

name: Manger
desc: During scoring, if your pastures cover at least 6/7/8/10 farm yard spaces, you get 1/2/3/4 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Lieutenant General
desc: For each field tile that another player places next to an existing field tile, you get 1 <FOOD> from the general supply. In round 14, you get 1 <GRAIN> instead.

name: Handcart
desc: Before each work phase, you can take 1 building resource from at most one <WOOD>/<CLAY>/<REED>/<STONE> accumulation space containing at least 6/5/4/4 building resources of the same type.

name: Furniture Maker
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <WOOD>. Each time you play an occupation after this one, you get 1 <WOOD> for each <FOOD> paid as occupation cost.

name: Mud Wallower
desc: Every fourth time you use an accumulation space, you get 1 <PIG>, held by this card.

name: Blighter
desc: When you play this card, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for each complete stage left to play. You may not play any more occupations.

name: Plow Builder
desc: You can build the Joinery when taking a __Minor Improvement__ action. If you use the Joinery (or an upgrade thereof) during the harvest, you can pay 1 <FOOD> to plow 1 field.

name: Catcher
desc: Each time you place your 1st/2nd/3rd person in a round on a building resource accumulation space with exactly 5/4/3 building resources, you get 1 <FOOD>.

name: Lumberjack
desc: You immediately get 1 <WOOD>. Additionally, place 1 <WOOD> on each of the next round spaces, up to the number of fences you built. At the start of these rounds, you get the <WOOD>.

name: Carpenter's Yard
desc: You can build the __Joinery__ and __Well__ major improvement even when taking a __Minor Improvement__ action, or you can build both with a single __Major Improvement__ action.

name: Large Pottery
desc: [Anytime]
<CLAY> <ARROW> 2<FOOD>
[Scoring]
3/5/6/7<CLAY> <ARROW-1X> 1/2/3/4<SCORE>

name: Stone House Reconstruction
desc: At any time, you can renovate your clay house to a stone house without placing a person. (You must pay the normal renovation cost.)

name: Sundial
desc: At the end of the work phases of rounds 7 and 9, you can take a __Sow__ action without placing a person.

name: Forest Tallyman
desc: Each time both the __Forest__ and __Clay Pit__ accumulation spaces are occupied, you can use this card as an action space to get 2 <CLAY> and 3 <WOOD>.

name: Loppers
desc: Each time you build 1 or more fences, you can also use this card to exchange 1 <WOOD> and 1 <FENCE> in your supply for 2 <FOOD> and 1 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Plumber
desc: Each time after you use the __Major Improvement__ action space, you can take a __Renovation__ action, paying 2 <CLAY> or 2 <STONE> less for the renovation.

name: Cattle Feeder
desc: Each time you use the __Grain Seeds__ action space, you can also buy 1 <CATTLE> for 1 <FOOD>.

name: Farmstead
desc: After each turn in which you make at least one unused farmyard space used, you get 1 <FOOD>.

name: Chairman
desc: Each time another player uses the __Meeting Place__ action space, both they and you get 1 <FOOD> (before taking the actions). If you use it, you get 1 <FOOD>.

name: Braid Maker
desc: Each harvest, you can use this card to exchange 1 <REED> for 2 <FOOD>. You can build the  __Basketmaker's Workshop__ for 1 <REED> and 1 <STONE> even when taking a __Minor Improvement__ action.

name: Water Gully
desc: Place 1 <CATTLE>, 1 <GRAIN>, and 1 <CATTLE> on the next 3 round spaces (in that order). At the start of these rounds, you get the respective good.

name: Shaving Horse
desc: Each time after you obtain at least 1 <WOOD>, if you then have 5 or more <WOOD> in your supply, you can exchange 1 <WOOD> for 3 <FOOD>. With 7 or more <WOOD>, you must do so.

name: Mineralogist
desc: Each time you use a clay/stone accumulation space, you also get 1 of the other good, <STONE>/<CLAY>.

name: Roof Ballaster
desc: When you play this card, you can immediately pay 1 <FOOD> to get 1 <STONE> for each room you have.

name: Herring Pot
desc: Each time you use the __Fishing__ accumulation space, place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next 3 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Excursion to the Quarry
desc: You immediately get a number of <STONE> equal to the number of people you have.

name: Gift Basket
desc: When you play this card, if you have exactly 2/3/4/5 rooms, you immediately get 1 <VEGETABLE>/<FOOD>/<GRAIN>/<VEGETABLE>.

name: Puppeteer
desc: Each time another player uses the __Traveling Players__ accumulation space, you can pay them 1 <FOOD> to immediately play an occupation without paying an occupation cost.

name: Forest Owner
desc: This card is an action space for all. If another player uses it, they get 3 <WOOD> and must give you 1 <WOOD> from the general supply. If you use it, you get 4 <WOOD>.

name: Omnifarmer
desc: Each harvest, you can place 1 harvested crop or 1 newborn animal on this card, irretrievably. Once this game, if there are 2/3/4/5 different goods on this, you get 3/5/7/9 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Iron Oven
desc: [__Bake Bread__ action:]
<GRAIN> <ARROW-1X> 6<FOOD>
When you play this card, you can immediately take a __Bake Bread__ action.

name: Wooden Shed
desc: This card can only be played via a __Major Improvement__ action. It provides room for one person. You may no longer renovate.

name: Breeder Buyer
desc: Each time you build at least 1 wood/clay/stone room and at least 1 stable on the same turn, you also get 1 <SHEEP>/<PIG>/<CATTLE>.

name: Cattle Farm
desc: For each pasture you have, you can keep 1 <CATTLE> on this card.

name: Material Deliveryman
desc: Each time any player (including you) takes 5/6/7/8+ goods from an accumulation space, you get 1 <WOOD>/<CLAY>/<REED>/<STONE> from the general supply.

name: Domestician Expert
desc: You can keep 2 sheep on the border between each pair of orthogonally adjacent rooms.

name: Large-Scale Farmer
desc: Each time after you use the __Farm Expansion__ or __Major Improvement__ action space while the other is unoccupied, you can pay 1 <FOOD> to use that other space with the same person.

name: Wildlife Reserve
desc: This card can hold up to 1 <SHEEP>, 1 <PIG>, and 1 <CATTLE>.

name: Crudit
desc: When you play this card, you can immediately buy exactly 1 <VEGETABLE> for 3 <FOOD>. At any time, you can discard 1 <VEGETABLE> on top of another <VEGETABLE> in a field to get 4 <FOOD>.

name: Rock Beater
desc: You can use an action space providing both stone and a different building resource even if it is occupied by another player. Stone rooms cost you 2 <STONE> less each.

name: Misanthropy
desc: During scoring, if you have exactly 4/3/2 people, you get 2/3/5 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Syrup Tap
desc: Each time you get at least 1 <WOOD> from an action space, place 1 <FOOD> on the next round space. At the start of that round, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Claypipe
desc: In the returning home phase of each round, if you gained at least 7 building resources in the preceding work phase, you get 2 <FOOD>.

name: Paper Maker
desc: Immediately before playing each occupation after this one, you can pay 1 <WOOD> total to get 1 <FOOD> for each occupation you have in front of you.

name: Sack Cart
desc: Place 1 <GRAIN> each on the remaining spaces for rounds 5, 8, 11, and 14. At the start of these rounds, you get the <GRAIN>.

name: Woodcraft
desc: Each time you use a wood accumulation space, if immediately afterward you have at most 5 <WOOD> in your supply, you get 1 <FOOD>.

name: Food Merchant
desc: For each <GRAIN> you harvest from a field, you can buy 1 <VEGETABLE> for 3 <FOOD>. If you harvest the last <GRAIN> from a field, the <VEGETABLE> costs you only 2 <FOOD>.

name: Patron
desc: Immediately before each time you play an occupation after this one (even before paying the occupation cost), you get 2 <FOOD>.

name: Party Organizer
desc: As soon as the next player but you gains their 5th person, you immediately get 8 <FOOD> (not retroactively). During scoring, if only you have 5 people, you get 3 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Civic Facade
desc: Before the start of each round, if you have more occupations than improvements in your hand, you get 1 <FOOD>.

name: Livestock Expert
desc: If you play this card in round 11 or before, choose an animal type: you immediately get a number of animals of that type equal to the number you already have on your farm.

name: Stone Custodian
desc: At the end of each work phase, you get 1 <FOOD> for each stone accumulation space with stone on it.

name: Sheep Rug
desc: You can use any __Wish for Children__ action space, even if it is occupied by another player's person.

name: Guest Room
desc: Immediately place any amount of <FOOD> from your supply on this card. Once per round, you can discard 1 <FOOD> from this card to place a person from your supply in that round.

name: Fodder Beets
desc: Place 1 <FOOD> on each remaining odd-numbered round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Agricultural Fertilizers
desc: Each time after you turn at least 2 unused spaces into used spaces in one action, you get an additional __Sow__ action.

name: Caravan
desc: This card provides room for 1 person.

name: Stew
desc: Each time you use the __Day Laborer__ action space, also place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next 4 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Bookcase
desc: Each time after you play an occupation, you get 1 <VEGETABLE>.

name: Blade Shears
desc: You immediately get your choice of 3 <FOOD>, or 1 <FOOD> for each sheep you have. (Keep the sheep.)

name: Pure Breeder
desc: You immediately get 1 <WOOD>. After each round that does not end with a harvest, you can breed exactly one type of animal. (This is not considered a breeding phase.)

name: Plowman
desc: Add 4, 7, and 10 to the current round and place a field tile on each corresponding round space. At the start of these rounds, you can plow the field for 1 <FOOD>.

name: Scythe
desc: During the field phase of each harvest, you can select exactly one of your fields and harvest all the crops planted in it.

name: Elder
desc: You can play this card at the start of the work phase of round 1 without placing a person. (This card has no effect other than counting as a played occupation.)

name: Building Expert
desc: Each time you use the __Resource Market__ action space with the 1st/2nd/3rd/4th/5th person you place, you also get 1 <WOOD>/<CLAY>/<REED>/<STONE>/<STONE>.

name: Stable Tree
desc: Each time you build 1 or more stables on your turn, place 1 <WOOD> on each of the next 3 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <WOOD>.

name: Charcoal Burner
desc: Each time any player (including you) plays or builds a <BAKE>-improvement, you get 1 <WOOD> and 1 <FOOD>.

name: Farm Store
desc: After the feeding phase of each harvest, you can exchange exactly 1 <FOOD> for 2 different building resources of your choice or 1 <VEGETABLE>.

name: Chicken Coop
desc: Place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next 8 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Godmother
desc: Each time you take a __Family Growth__ action, you also get 1 <VEGETABLE>.

name: Roman Pot
desc: Place 4 <FOOD> from the general supply on this card. At the start of each work phase, if you are the last player in turn order, move 1 <FOOD> from this card to your supply.

name: Calcium Fertilizers
desc: Each time you use a __Quarry__ accumulation space, add 1 additional good of the respective type to each of your planted fields growing a single type of crop.

name: Equipper
desc: Immediately after each time you use a wood accumulation space, you can play a minor improvement.

name: Cattle Whisperer
desc: Add 5 and 8 to the current round and place 1 <CATTLE> on each corresponding round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the <CATTLE>.

name: Craft Brewery
desc: In the feeding phase of each harvest, you can use this card to exchange 1 <GRAIN> from your supply plus 1 <GRAIN> from a field for 2 bonus <SCORE> and 4 <FOOD>.

name: Pulverizer Plow
desc: Immediately after each time you use a clay accumulation space, you can pay 1 <CLAY> to plow 1 field. If you do, place that 1 <CLAY> on the accumulation space.

name: Champion Breeder
desc: Each time you place 2 or 3+ newborn animals on your farm during the breeding phase of the harvest, you get 1 or 2 bonus <SCORE>, respectively.

name: Dolly's Mother
desc: You only require 1 <SHEEP> to breed sheep during the breeding phase of a harvest. This card can hold 1 <SHEEP>.

name: Stable Planner
desc: Add 3, 6, and 9 to the current round. You can place 1 stable on each corresponding round space. At the start of these rounds (not earlier), you can build the stable at no cost.

name: Childless
desc: At the start of each round, if you have at least 3 rooms but only 2 people, you get 1 <FOOD> and 1 crop of your choice (<GRAIN> or <VEGETABLE>)

name: Writing Chamber
desc: During scoring, you get a number of bonus <SCORE> equal to the total of negative points you have, to a maximum of 7 <SCORE>.

name: Lifting Machine
desc: At the end of each round that does not end with a harvest, you can move 1 <VEGETABLE> from one of your fields to your supply. (This is not considered a field phase.)

name: Conservator
desc: You can renovate your wooden house directly to stone without renovating it to clay first.

name: Manservant
desc: Once you live in a stone house, place 3 <FOOD> on each remaining round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Greengrocer
desc: Each time you use the __Grain Seeds__ action space, you also get 1 <VEGETABLE>.

name: Club House
desc: Place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next 4 round spaces and 1 <STONE> on the round space after that. At the start of these rounds, you get the respective good.

name: Pet Grower
desc: Each time you use an animal accumulation space, if afterward you have no animal in your house, you also get 1 <SHEEP>.

name: Emergency Seller
desc: When you play this card, you can immediately turn as many building resources into food as you have people:
<WOOD>/<CLAY> <ARROW> 2 <FOOD>
<REED>/<STONE> <ARROW> 3 <FOOD>

name: Pipe Smoker
desc: At the start of each harvest, if you have at least 1 grain field, you get 2<WOOD>.

name: Old Miser
desc: In the feeding phase of each harvest, each of your people requires 1less <FOOD>. During scoring, your people are worth 2 points each instead of 3.

name: Profiteering
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <FOOD>. Each time you use the __Day Laborer__ action space, you can exchange 1 building resource for another building resource.

name: Oven Site
desc: When you play this card, you get 2 <WOOD> and you can immediately build the __Clay Oven__ or __Stone Oven__ major improvement. Either way, it only costs you 1 <CLAY> and 1 <STONE>.

name: Sheep Walker
desc: At any time, you can exchange 1 <SHEEP> on your farmyard for either 1 <PIG>, 1 <VEGETABLE>, or 1 <STONE>.

name: Field Caretaker
desc: When you play this card, you can immediately exchange 0/1/3 <CLAY> for 1/2/3 <GRAIN>. This card is a field.

name: Pasture Master
desc: Each time you renovate, you get 2 <FOOD> and 1 additional animal of the respective type in each of your pastures with stable.

name: Assistant Tiller
desc: Each time you use the __Day Laborer__ action space, you can also plow 1 field.

name: Alchemists Lab
desc: This card is an action space for all. A player who uses it gets 1 building resource of each type they already have. If another player uses it, they must first pay you 1 <FOOD>.

name: Clay Puncher
desc: When you play this card and each time after you use a __Lessons__ action space or the __Clay Pit__ accumulation space, you get 1 <CLAY>.

name: Shepherd's Crook
desc: Each time you fence a new pasture covering at least 4 farmyard spaces, you immediately get 2 sheep on this pasture.

name: Clay Warden
desc: Each time another player uses the __Hollow__ accumulation space, you get 1 <CLAY>. In a 3-/4-player game, you also get 1 additional <CLAY>/<FOOD>.

name: Remodeling
desc: You immediately get 1 <CLAY> for each clay room and for each major improvement you have.

name: Archway
desc: This card is an action space for all. A player who uses it immediately gets 1 <FOOD>. Immediately before the returning home phase, they can use an unoccupied action space with the person from this card.

name: Child Ombudsman
desc: From round 5 on, if you have room in your house, at the end of each person action, you can take a __Family Growth__ action with that person. If you do, you get 2 negative <SCORE>.

name: Begging Student
desc: When you play this card, you must immediately take 1 <BEGGING> marker. At the start of each harvest, you can play 1 occupation without paying an occupation cost.

name: Ceilings
desc: Place 1 <WOOD> on the next 5 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <WOOD>. Remove the <WOOD> promised by this card from future round spaces the next time you renovate.

name: Confidant
desc: Place 1 <FOOD> from your supply on each of the next 2, 3, or 4 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD> back and your choice of a __Sow__ or __Build Fences__ action.

name: Clay Carrier
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 2 <CLAY>. At any time, but only once per round, you can buy 2 <CLAY> for 2 <FOOD>.

name: Potato Planter
desc: At the end of each work phase in which you occupy the __Clay Pit__ or __Reed Bank__ accumulation space while the respective other is unoccupied, you get 1 <VEGETABLE>.

name: Scullery
desc: At the start of each round, if you live in a wooden house, you get 1 <FOOD>.

name: Granary
desc: Place 1 <GRAIN> each on the remaining spaces for rounds 8, 10, and 12. At the start of these rounds, you get the <GRAIN>.

name: Stone Carver
desc: Each harvest, you can use this card to turn exactly 1 <STONE> into 3 <FOOD>.

name: Beer Tent Operator
desc: In the feeding phase of each harvest, you can use this card to turn 1 <WOOD> plus 1 <GRAIN> into 1 bonus <SCORE> and 2 <FOOD>.

name: Water Worker
desc: Each time after you use any of the __Fishing__, __Reed Bank__, __Day Laborer__ spaces or the action space of round 4, you get 1 additional <REED>.

name: Hewer
desc: From round 3 on, at the end of each work phase in which all clay accumulation spaces are unoccupied, you get 1 <STONE> and 1 <FOOD>.

name: Piggy Bank
desc: At the end of each work phase, you can place 1 <FOOD> on this card, irretrievably. At any time, you can discard 6 <FOOD> from this card to build a major improvement at no cost.

name: Ox Skull
desc: During scoring, if you have no <CATTLE>, you get 3 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Recreational Carpenter
desc: At the end of each work phase in which you did not use the __Meeting Place__ action space, you can take a __Build Rooms__ action without placing a person.

name: Game Trade
desc: You immediately get 1 <PIG> and 1 <CATTLE>. (effectively, you are exchanging 2 <SHEEP> for 1 <PIG> and 1 <CATTLE>.)

name: Kelp Gatherer
desc: Each time another player uses the __Fishing__ accumulation space, they get 1 additional <FOOD> and you get 1 <VEGETABLE>.

name: Small Trader
desc: Each time you take a __Major or Minor Improvement__ action to play an improvement from your hand, you also get 3 <FOOD>.

name: Fellow Grazer
desc: During scoring, you get 2 bonus <SCORE> for each pasture you have covering at least 3 farmyard spaces.

name: Wood Pile
desc: You immediately get a number of <WOOD> equal to the number of people you have on accumulation spaces.

name: Market Stall
desc: You immediately get 1 <VEGETABLE>. (Effectively, you are exchanging 1 <GRAIN> for 1 <VEGETABLE>).

name: Collector
desc: This card is an action space for you only. When you use it for the 1st/2nd/3rd/4th time, you get 1 <BEGGING> marker and 6/7/8/9 different good of your choice.

name: Hide Farmer
desc: During scoring, you can pay 1 <FOOD> each for any number of unused farmyard spaces. You do not lose points for these spaces.

name: Oyster Eater
desc: Each time the __Fishing__ accumulation space is used, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> and must skip placing your next person that round. (You can place the person on a later turn.)

name: Visionary
desc: If you play this card in round 4 or before, you get 1 <STONE>, 1<VEGETABLE>, and 2 <PIG>. You cannot grow your family until round 11, unless all other players already have.

name: Barn Cats
desc: If you have 1/2/3/4 stables, place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next 2/3/4/5 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Full Peasant
desc: Each time after you use the __Grain Utilization__ or __Fencing__ action space while the other is unoccupied, you can pay 1 <FOOD> to use the other space with the same person.

name: Truffle Searcher
desc: This card can hold a number of <PIG> equal to the number of completed feeding phases.

name: Home Brewer
desc: After the field phase of each harvest, you can use this card to turn exactly 1 <GRAIN> into your choice of 3 <FOOD> or 1 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Excavator
desc: Each time after you use the __Day Laborer__ action space, you get 1 additional <WOOD> and <CLAY>, and you can buy 1 <STONE> for 1 <FOOD>.

name: Wood Cart
desc: Each time you use a wood accumulation space, you get 2 additional <WOOD>.

name: Diligent Farmer
desc: When you play this card, if you would score the maximum 4 points in 3 scoring categories (including fenced stables), you can extend your house by 1 room at no cost.

name: Asparagus Knife
desc: In the returning home phase of rounds 8, 10, and 12, you can take 1 <VEGETABLE> from exactly 1 vegetable field. You can immediately exchange it for 3 <FOOD> and 1 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Salter
desc: At any time, you can pay 1 <SHEEP>/<PIG>/<CATTLE> from your farm. If you do, place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next 3/5/7 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Established Person
desc: If your house has exactly 2 rooms, immediately renovate it without paying any building resources. If you do, you can immediately afterward take a __Build Fences__ action.

name: Canoe
desc: Each time you use the __Fishing__ accumulation space, you get an additional 1 <FOOD> and 1 <REED>.

name: Bed Maker
desc: Each time you add rooms to your house, you can also pay 1 <WOOD> and 1 <GRAIN> to immediately get a __Family Growth with Room Only__ action.

name: Clutterer
desc: During scoring, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for each card played after this one that has "accumulation space(s)" in its text.

name: Reed Pond
desc: Place 1 <REED> on each of the next 3 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <REED>.

name: Hand Truck
desc: Each time before you take a __Bake Bread__ action, you also get 1 <GRAIN> for each of your people occupying an accumulation space.

name: Loam Pit
desc: Each time you use the __Day Laborer__ action space, you also get 3 <CLAY>.

name: Seed Researcher
desc: Each time any people return from both the __Grain Seeds__ and __Vegetable Seeds__ action spaces, you get 2 <FOOD> and you can play 1 occupation, without paying an occupation cost.

name: Skimmer Plow
desc: Each time you use the __Farmland__ or __Cultivation__  action space, you can plow 2 fields instead of 1. Each time you sow, you must place 1 fewer good on each field you sow.

name: Drinking Trough
desc: Each of your pastures (with or without a stable) can hold up to 2 more animals.

name: Mummy's Boy
desc: Once per round, when placing a person after your first two, you can place it on the action space with your 2nd person and use that space again, unless it is on the __Meeting Place__ action space.

name: Carpenter's Hammer
desc: Each time you build at least 2 wood/clay/stone rooms at once, you get a total discount of 2 <REED> as well as 2 <WOOD>/3 <CLAY>/4 <STONE>.

name: Seatmate
desc: You can use the action space on round space 13 even if it is occupied by one or more people of the players to your immediate left and right.

name: Scholar
desc: Once you live in a stone house, at the start of each round, you can play an occupation for an occupation cost of 1 <FOOD>, or a minor improvement (by paying its cost).

name: Soldier
desc: During scoring, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for each <STONE> + <WOOD> pair in your supply. You cannot score additional points for the resources scored with this card.

name: Recruitment
desc: From round 5 on, provided you have room in your house, each time you get a __Minor Improvement__ action, you can take a __Family Growth__ action instead.
prerequisite: No People Left in the House

name: Storeroom
desc: During scoring, you get  bonus <SCORE> for each pair of <GRAIN> plus <VEGETABLE> you have (considering all crops in your supply and fields), rounded up.

name: Pitchfork
desc: Each time you use the __Grain Seeds__ action space, if the __Farmland__ action space is occupied you also get 3 <FOOD>.

name: Perennial Rye
desc: Each round that does not end with a harvest, you can pay 1 <GRAIN> to breed exactly 1 type of animal. (This is not considered a breeding phase.)

name: Sowing Master
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <WOOD>. Each time after you use the __Grain Utilization__ or __Cultivation__ action space, you get 2 <FOOD>.

name: Grain Thief
desc: Each time you would harvest a grain field, you can leave the grain on the field and take 1 <GRAIN> from the general supply instead.

name: Parvenu
desc: If you play this card in round 7 or before, choose <CLAY> or <REED>: you immediately get a number of that building resource equal to the number you already have in your supply.

name: Roof Ladder
desc: Each time you renovate, you pay 1 fewer <REED> and, at the end of the action, you get 1 <STONE>.

name: Blackberry Farmer
desc: Each time you build fences, place 1 <FOOD> on each remaining round space, up to the number of fences just built. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Heirloom
desc: (This card has no additional effect.)

name: Forest School
desc: You can consider the __Lessons__ action spaces not occupied. You can replace each <FOOD> that an occupation costs with <WOOD>.

name: Wool Blankets
desc: During scoring, if you live in a wooden/clay/stone house by then, you get 3/2/0 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Seaweed Fertilizer
desc: Each time after you take an unconditional __Sow__ action, you get 1 <GRAIN> from the general supply. From round 11 on, you can get 1 <VEGETABLE> instead.

name: Automatic Water Trough
desc: If you can accommodate the animal, you can immediately buy 1 <SHEEP>/<PIG>/<CATTLE> for 0/1/2 <FOOD>.

name: Plow Maker
desc: Each time you use the __Farmland__ or __Cultivation__ action space, you can pay 1 <FOOD> to plow 1 additional field.

name: Animal Husbandry Worker
desc: If there are still 3/6/9 complete rounds left to play, you immediately get 2/3/4 <WOOD> and a __Build Fences__ action. During scoring, each player with the most pastures gets 2 <SCORE>.

name: Upholstery
desc: Each time you build or play an improvement after this one, you can place 1 <REED> on this card, irretrievably, to get 1 bonus <SCORE>, up to the number of rooms in your house.

name: Task Artisan
desc: When you play this card and each time a stone accumulation space appears on a round space in the preparation phase, you get 1 <WOOD> and a __Minor Improvement__ action.

name: Nutrition Expert
desc: At the start of each round, you can exchange a set comprised of 1 animal of any type, 1 <GRAIN>, and 1 <VEGETABLE> for 5 <FOOD> and 2 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Prodigy
desc: If this is your 1st occupation, you immediately get 1 <SCORE> for each improvement you have. (This will not apply to improvements played after this card.)

name: Chapel
desc: This is an action space for all. A player who uses it gets 3 bonus <SCORE>. If another player uses it, they must first pay you 1 <GRAIN>.

name: Work Certificate
desc: Each time after you use an action space, you can take 1 building resource from a building resource accumulation space with at least 4 building resources on it.

name: Gypsy's Crock
desc: Each time you use a cooking improvement to turn 2 goods into <FOOD> at the same time, you get 1 additional <FOOD>.

name: Saddler
desc: Each time after you build a major improvement, you can pay 1 <FOOD> to plow 1 field.

name: Woolgrower
desc: This card can hold a number of <SHEEP> equal to the number of completed feeding phases.

name: Small-scale Farmer
desc: As long as you live in a house with exactly 2 rooms, at the start of each round, you get 1 <WOOD>.

name: Stable Master
desc: When you play this card, you can immediately build exactly 1 stable for 1 <WOOD>. Exactly one of your unfenced stables can hold up to 3 animals of one type.

name: Layabout
desc: When you play this card, you must skip the next harvest. (You also do not have to feed your family that harvest.)

name: Fisherman's Friend
desc: At the start of each round, if there is more <FOOD> on the __Traveling Players__ than on the __Fishing__ accumulation space, you get the difference from the general supply.

name: Private Forest
desc: Place 1 <WOOD> on each remaining even-numbered round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the <WOOD>.

name: Renovation Materials
desc: Immediately renovate to clay at no cost. (You must pay the cost of this card though.)

name: Packaging Artist
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <GRAIN>. Each time you get a __Minor Improvement__ action, you can take a __Bake Bread__ action instead.

name: Writing Boards
desc: You immediately get 1 <WOOD> for each occupation you have in front of you.

name: Stable Milker
desc: Each time you build at least 2 stables on the same turn, you also get 1 <CATTLE>.

name: Pen Builder
desc: At any time, you can discard 1 <WOOD> from your supply. This card can hold two animals of any type for each <WOOD> discarded this way.

name: Basket
desc: Immediately after each time you use a wood accumulation space, you can exchange 2 <WOOD> for 3 <FOOD>. If you do, place those 2 <WOOD> on the accumulation space.

name: Hayloft Barn
desc: Place 4 <FOOD> on this card. Each time you obtain at least 1 <GRAIN>, you also get 1 <FOOD> from this card. Once it is empty, you get a __Family Growth Even without Room__ action.

name: Grange
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <FOOD>.
prerequisite: 6 Field Tiles and All Animal Types

name: Forest Stone
desc: Place 2 <FOOD> on this card. Each time you use a wood accumulation space, move 1 of these <FOOD> to your supply. Each time you use a stone accumulation space, add 2 <FOOD> to this card.

name: Clay Firer
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 2 <CLAY>. At any time, you can turn <CLAY> into <STONE>: you get 1 <STONE> for 2 <CLAY>, and 2 <STONE> for 3 <CLAY>.

name: Interim Storage
desc: Each time you use a clay/reed/stone accumulation space, place 1 <WOOD>/<CLAY>/<REED> on this card. At the start of rounds 7, 11, and 14, move all the goods on this card to your supply.

name: Skillful Renovator
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <WOOD> and 1 <CLAY>. Each time after you renovate, you get a number of <WOOD> equal to the number of people you placed that round.

name: Freemason
desc: As long as you live in a <CLAY>/<STONE> house with exactly 2 rooms, at the start of each work phase, you get 2 <CLAY>/<STONE>.

name: Harpooner
desc: Each time you use the __Fishing__ space you can also pay 1 <WOOD> to get 1 <FOOD> for each person you have, and 1 <REED>

name: Stable Architect
desc: During scoring, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for each unfenced stable in your farmyard.

name: Basketmaker's Wife
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <REED> and 1 <FOOD>. At any time, you can turn 1 <REED> into 2 <FOOD>.

name: Swing Plow
desc: Place 4 field tiles on this card. Each time you use the __Farmland__ action space, you can also plow up to 2 fields from this card.

name: Trap Builder
desc: Each time you use the __Day Laborer__ action space, place 1 <FOOD>, 1 <FOOD>, and 1 <PIG> on the next 3 round spaces, respectively. At the start of these rounds, you get the good.

name: Truffle Slicer
desc: Each time you use a wood accumulation space, if you have at least 1 <PIG>, you can pay 1 <FOOD> for 1 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Pottery Yard
desc: During the scoring, if there are at least 2 orthogonally adjacent unused spaces in your farm, you get 2 bonus <SCORE>. (You still get the negative points for those unused spaces.

name: Horse-Drawn Boat
desc: Alternate placing 1 <FOOD> and 1 <SHEEP> on each remaining round space, starting with <FOOD>. At the start of these rounds, you get the respective good.

name: Feed Pellets
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <SHEEP>. In the feeding phase of each harvest, you can exchange exactly 1 <VEGETABLE> for 1 animal of a type you already have.

name: Field Merchant
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <WOOD> and 1 <REED>. Each time you decline a __Minor/Major Improvement__ action, you get 1 <FOOD>/<VEGETABLE> instead.

name: Schnapps Distillery
desc: In each feeding phase, you can use this card to turn exactly 1 <VEGETABLE> into 5 <FOOD>. During scoring, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> each for your 5th and 6th <VEGETABLE>.

name: Town Hall
desc: In the feeding phase of each harvest, if you live in a clay or stone house, you get 1 or 2 <FOOD>, respectively.

name: Animal Feeder
desc: On the __Day Laborer__ action space, you also get your choice of 1 <SHEEP> or 1 <GRAIN>. Instead of that good, you can buy 1 <PIG> for 1 <FOOD> or 1 <CATTLE> for 2 <FOOD>.

name: Seed Almanac
desc: Each time after you play a minor improvement after this one, you can pay 1 <FOOD> to plow 1 field.

name: Raised Bed
desc: At the start of each harvest, you get 4 <FOOD>.

name: Miller
desc: You can immediately build a <BAKE>-improvement by paying its cost. Each time another player uses the __Grain Seeds__ action space, you can take a __Bake Bread__ action.

name: Mayor Candidate
desc: You immediately get 2 <WOOD> and 2 <STONE>. During scoring, you get 1 negative point for each <WOOD> and each <STONE> in your supply. You can no longer discard <WOOD> or <STONE>.

name: Lodger
desc: This card provides room for one person, but only until the returning home phase of round 9. If, by then, there is no room elsewhere for that person, remove it from play.

name: Artisan District
desc: During scoring, you get 2/5/8 bonus <SCORE> for having 3/4/5 major improvements from the bottom row of the supply board.

name: Bee Statue
desc: Pile (from bottom to top) 1 <VEGETABLE>, 1 <STONE>, 1 <GRAIN>, 1 <STONE>, 1 <GRAIN> on this card. Each time you use the __Day Laborer__ action space, you get the top good.

name: Estate Master
desc: Once you have no unused farmyard spaces left, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for each <VEGETABLE> that you harvest.

name: Petrified Wood
desc: Immediately exchange up to 3 <WOOD> for 1 <STONE> each.

name: Master Workman
desc: Each time before you use an action space card on round spaces 1/2/3/4, you get 1 <WOOD>/<CLAY>/<REED>/<STONE>.

name: Bohemian
desc: At the start of each returning home phase, if at least one __Lessons__ action space is unoccupied, you get 1 <FOOD>.

name: Milk Jug
desc: Each time any player (including you) uses the __Cattle Market__ accumulation space, you get 3 <FOOD>, and each other player gets 1 <FOOD>.

name: Feeding Dish
desc: Each time you use an animal accumulation space while already having an animal of that type, you get 1 <GRAIN>.

name: Imitator
desc: If you have a person on the __Day Laborer__ action space, you can use non-accumulating round 1-9 action spaces even if they are occupied.

name: Shepherd's Whistle
desc: At the start of the breeding phase of each harvest, if you have at least 1 unfenced stable without an animal, you get 1 <SHEEP>.

name: Facades Carving
desc: When you play this card, you can exchange any number of <FOOD> for 1 bonus <SCORE> each, up to the number of completed harvests.
prerequisite: Wood in Your Supply >= Current Round

name: Spice Trader
desc: If you play this card in round 4 or before, place 3 <VEGETABLE> on the space for round 11. At the start of that round, you get the <VEGETABLE>.

name: Smuggler
desc: In the feeding phase of each harvest, you can exchange up to 2 goods as follows:
[<WOOD> <ARROW> <GRAIN>]
or
[<GRAIN> <ARROW> <STONE>]

name: Cow Patty
desc: Each time you sow in a field that is orthogonally adjacent to a pasture, you can place 1 additional good of the planted type in it.

name: Pumpernickel
desc: You immediately get 4 <FOOD>. (Effectively, you are turning 1 <GRAIN> into 4 <FOOD>.)

name: Furniture Carpenter
desc: Each harvest, if any player (including you) owns the Joinery or an upgrade thereof, you can buy exactly 1 bonus <SCORE> for 2 <FOOD>.

name: Cooperative Plower
desc: Each time you use the __Farmland__ action space while the __Grain Seeds__ action space is occupied, you can plow 1 additional field.

name: Beer Stein
desc: Each time you take a __Bake Bread__ action, you can use this card once to turn 1 <GRAIN> into 2 <FOOD> and 1 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Rolling Pin
desc: In the returning home phase of each round, if you have more <CLAY> than <WOOD> in your supply, you get 1 <FOOD>.

name: Wares Salesman
desc: Each time any player (including you) plays or builds a card that lets them turn building resources into <FOOD>, you get exactly 1 corresponding building resource and 1 <REED>.

name: Boar Spear
desc: Each time you get at least 1 <PIG> outside of the breeding phase of a harvest, you can immediately turn them into 4 <FOOD> each.

name: Bale of Straw
desc: At the start of each harvest, if you have at least 3 grain fields (including field cards with planted grain), you get 2 <FOOD>.

name: Tasting
desc: Each time you use a __Lessons__ action space, before paying the occupation cost, you can exchange 1 <GRAIN> for 4 <FOOD>.

name: Master Tanner
desc: For each <PIG> or <CATTLE> you turn into <FOOD>, you can place 1 of that <FOOD> on this card. While its <FOOD> equals your number of rooms, this card provides room for 1 person.

name: Organic Farmer
desc: During the scoring, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for each pasture containing at least 1 animal while having unused capacity for at least three more animals.

name: Clay Plasterer
desc: Renovating to clay only costs you exactly 1 <CLAY> and 1 <REED>. Each clay room only costs you 3 <CLAY> and 2 <REED> to build.

name: Farmers Market
desc: You immediately get 1 <VEGETABLE>. (Effectively, you are buying 1 <VEGETABLE> for 2 <FOOD>.)

name: Beneficiary
desc: If this is your 3rd occupation, you can immediately play another occupation for an occupation cost of 1 <FOOD> and/or play 1 minor improvement by paying its cost.

name: Buyer
desc: Each time another player uses a reed, stone, sheep, or wild boar accumulation space, you can pay them 1 <FOOD> to get 1 good of the respective type from the general supply.

name: Sleeping Corner
desc: You can use any __Wish for Children__ action space even if it is occupied by one other player's person.

name: Oven Firing Boy
desc: Each time you use a wood accumulation space, you get an additional __Bake Bread__ action.

name: Moonshine
desc: Randomly select an occupation in your hand. Either play it for an occupation cost of 2 <FOOD>, or give it to the next player.

name: Wood Expert
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 2 <WOOD>. Each improvement costs you up to 2 <WOOD> less, if you pay 1 <FOOD> instead.

name: Writing Desk
desc: Each time you use a __Lessons__ action space, you can play 1 additional occupation for an occupation cost of 2 <FOOD>.

name: Acorns Basket
desc: Place 1 <PIG> on each of the next 2 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <PIG>.

name: Private Teacher
desc: Each time you use the __Grain Seeds__ action space when any __Lessons__ action space is occupied, you can also play an occupation for an occupation cost of 1 <FOOD>.

name: Fodder Chamber
desc: During scoring in a game with 1/2/3/4+ players, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for every 7th/5th/4th/3rd animal on your farm.

name: Gritter
desc: At the end of each action in which you sow vegetables in a field, you get 1 <FOOD> for each vegetable field you have (including the new ones).

name: Storehouse Steward
desc: Each time you take exactly 2/3/4/5 <FOOD> from a food accumulation space, you also get 1 <STONE>/<REED>/<CLAY>/<WOOD>. (If you take 6 or more <FOOD>, you do not get a bonus good).

name: Game Catcher
desc: When you play this card, pay 1 <FOOD> for each remaining harvest to immediately get 1 <CATTLE> and 1 <PIG>.

name: Ropemaker
desc: At the end of each harvest, you get 1 <REED> from the general supply.

name: Pet Lover
desc: Each time you use an accumulation space providing exactly 1 animal, you can leave it on the space and get one from the general supply instead, as well as 3 <FOOD> and 1 <GRAIN>.

name: Cheese Fondue
desc: Each time you bake at least 1 <GRAIN> into bread, you get 1 additional <FOOD> if you have at least 1<SHEEP> and (another) 1 additional <FOOD> if you have at least 1 <CATTLE>.

name: Swimming Class
desc: In the returning home phase of each round, if you return a person from the __Fishing__ accumulation space, you get 2 bonus <SCORE> for each newborn that you return home.

name: Oriental Fireplace
desc: [Anytime]
<VEGETABLE> <ARROW> 4<FOOD>      <SHEEP> <ARROW> 3<FOOD>
<CATTLE> <ARROW> 5<FOOD>
[__Bake Bread__ action:]
<GRAIN> <ARROW> 2<FOOD>

name: Stone Buyer
desc: When you play this card, you can immediately buy exactly 2 <STONE> for 1 <FOOD>. From the next round on, once per round, you can buy 1 <STONE> for 2 <FOOD>.

name: Tree Inspector
desc: This card is a __1 <WOOD>__ accumulation space for you only. Each time the newly revealed action space card is a __Quarry__ accumulation space, you must discard all <WOOD> from this card.

name: Credit
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 5 <FOOD>. At the end of each round that does not end with a harvest, you must pay 1 <FOOD>, or else take a <BEGGING> marker.

name: Seed Seller
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <GRAIN>. Each time you use the __Grain Seeds__ action space, you get 1 additional <GRAIN>.

name: Turnwrest Plow
desc: Place 2 field tiles on this card. Each time you use the __Farmland__ or __Cultivation__ action space, you can also plow up to 2 fields from this card.

name: Interior Decorator
desc: Each time you renovate, place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next 6 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Luxurious Hostel
desc: During scoring, if you then have more stone rooms than people, you get 4 bonus <SCORE>. You can only use one card to get bonus points for your stone house.

name: Comb and Cutter
desc: Each time you use the __Day Laborer__ action space, you get 1 additional <FOOD> for each <SHEEP> on the __Sheep Market__ accumulation space, up to a maximum of 4 additional <FOOD>.

name: Pattern Maker
desc: Each time another player renovates, you can exchange exactly 2 <WOOD> for 1 <GRAIN>, 1 <FOOD>, and 1 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Bed in the Grain Field
desc: At the start of the next harvest, you get a __Family Growth__ action if you have room for the newborn.

name: Lutenist
desc: Each time another player uses the __Traveling Players__ accumulation space, you get 1 <FOOD> and 1 <WOOD>. Immediately after, you can buy exactly 1 <VEGETABLE> for 2 <FOOD>.

name: Dwelling Plan
desc: You can immediately take a __Renovation__ action.

name: Animal Driver
desc: At the start of each harvest, if you have 1/2/3+ fenced stables, you get 1 <SHEEP>/<PIG>/<CATTLE>.

name: Tea Time
desc: Immediately return your person on the __Grain Utilization__ action space home; you can place it again later this round.

name: Sleight of Hand
desc: When you play this card, you can immediately exchange up to 4 building resources for an equal number of other building resources.

name: Grassland Harrow
desc: Add 1 to the current round for each building resource in your supply and place 1 field on the corresponding round space. A the start of the round, you can plow the field.

name: Bunk Beds
desc: Once you have 4 rooms, your house can hold 5 people.

name: Basket Weaver
desc: When you play this card, immediately build the __Basketmaker's Workshop__ major improvement for 1 <STONE> and 1 <REED>.

name: Apiary
desc: At the end of each work phase, you can sow exactly 1 crop on 1 field.

name: Geologist
desc: Each time you use the __Forest__ or __Reed Bank__ accumulation space, you also get 1 <CLAY>. In games with 3 or more players, this also applies to the __Clay Pit__.

name: Slurry
desc: In the breeding phase of each harvest, if you get newborn animals of at least two types, you also get a __Sow__ action.

name: Zigzag Harrow
desc: You can immediately plow 1 field such that it completes a "zigzag" pattern.

name: Stable Sergeant
desc: When you play this card, you can pay 2 <FOOD> to get 1 <SHEEP>, 1 <PIG>, and 1 <CATTLE>, but only if you can accommodate all three animals on your farm.

name: Ebonist
desc: Each harvest, you can use this card to turn exactly 1 <WOOD> into 1 <FOOD> and 1 <GRAIN>.

name: Lazybones
desc: Place (up to) 1 <STABLE> each on __Grain Seeds__, __Farmland__, __Day Laborer__, and __Farm Expansion__. Build the <STABLE> at no cost when another player uses that action space.

name: House Steward
desc: If there are still 1/3/6/9 complete rounds left to play, you immediately get 1/2/3/4 <WOOD>. During scoring, each player with the most rooms gets 3 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Sheep Agent
desc: You can keep 1 <SHEEP> on this card for each occupation card in front of you (including this one), unless it is already able to hold animals.

name: Roughcaster
desc: Each time you build at least 1 clay room or renovate your house from clay to stone, you also get 3 <FOOD>.

name: Claw Knife
desc: Each time you use the __Sheep Market__ accumulation space, place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next 2 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Animal Bedding
desc: You can keep 1 additional animal (of the same type) in each of your unfenced stables, and 2 additional animals (of the same type) in each pasture with stable.

name: Veggie Lover
desc: [Harvest]
<GRAIN_VEG_STACK> <ARROW-1X> 6<FOOD>
[Scoring]
1/2/3 <GRAIN_VEG_STACK> <ARROW-1X> 2/4/6 <SCORE>

name: Vegetable Slicer
desc: Each time you upgrade a Fireplace to a Cooking Hearth, you immediately get 2 <WOOD> and 1 <VEGETABLE> (not retroactively).

name: Threshing Board
desc: Each time you use the __Farmland__ or __Cultivation__ action space, you get an additional __Bake Bread__ action.

name: Stone Importer
desc: In the breeding phase of the 1st/2nd/3rd/4th/5th/6th harvest, you can use this card to buy exactly 2 <STONE> for 2/2/3/3/4/1 <FOOD>.

name: Clay Deliveryman
desc: Place 1 <CLAY> on each remaining space for rounds 6 to 14. At the start of these rounds, you get the <CLAY>.

name: Firewood Collector
desc: Each time you use the __Farmland__, __Grain Seeds__, __Grain Utilization__, or __Cultivation__ action space, at the end of that turn, you get 1 <WOOD>.

name: Wild Greens
desc: Each time you sow, you get 1 <FOOD> for every different type of good that you sow.

name: Carpenter's Axe
desc: Each time after you use a wood accumulation space, if you then have at least 7 <WOOD> in your supply, you can build exactly 1 stable for 1 <WOOD>.

name: Ambition
desc: Each time you get a __Minor Improvement__ action on an action space, you can build a major improvement instead of playing a minor one.

name: Elephantgrass Plant
desc: Immediately after each harvest, you can use this card to exchange exactly 1 <REED> for 1 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Game Provider
desc: Immediately before each harvest, you can discard 1/3/4 <GRAIN> from different fields to get 1/2/3 <PIG>.

name: Double-Turn Plow
desc: When you play this card, you can immediately plow up to 2 fields.

name: Feed Fence
desc: For each new stable you build, you get 1 <FOOD> for your last one, get 3 <FOOD>. Each time you build stables, you can build exactly 1 stable for 1 <CLAY> instead of 2 <WOOD>.

name: Night-School Student
desc: Each returning home phase in which no player returns a person from a __Lessons__ action space, you can play an occupation for an occupation cost of 1 <FOOD>.

name: Tax Collector
desc: Once you live in a stone house, at the start of each round, you get your choice of 2 <WOOD>, 2 <CLAY>, 1 <REED>, or 1 <STONE>.

name: Potato Harvester
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 3 <FOOD>. For each <VEGETABLE> you get from your fields during the field phase of the harvest, you get 1 additional <FOOD>.

name: Trimmer
desc: In each work phase, after you enclose at least one farmyard space, you get 2 <STONE>. (Subdividing an existing pasture does not count.)

name: Forestry Studies
desc: Each time after you use the __Forest__ accumulation space, you can return 2 <WOOD> to that space to play 1 occupation without paying an occupation costs.

name: Elder Baker
desc: This card is an action space for you only. When you use it, you get 3<GRAIN>. You can build the __Stone Oven__ major improvement even when taking a __Minor Improvement__ action.

name: Pole Barns
desc: You can immediately build up to 3 stables at no cost. (You must pay the cost of this card though.)

name: Henpecked Husband
desc: Each time you take a __Build Rooms__ action with the second person you place, return the first person you placed home, unless it is on the __Meeting Place__ action space.

name: Animal Reeve
desc: If there are still 1/3/6/9 complete rounds left to play, you immediately get 1/2/3/4 <WOOD>. During scoring, each player with 2/3/4+ animals of each type gets 1/3/5 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Studio Boat
desc: Each time you use the __Traveling Players__ accumulation space, you also get 1 bonus <SCORE>. In games with 1-3 players, this card is considered __Traveling Players__ (same effect as __Fishing__).

name: Grocer
desc: Pile the following goods on this card (<WOOD>, <GRAIN>, <REED>, <STONE>, <VEGETABLE>, <CLAY>, <REED>, <VEGETABLE>). At any time, you can buy the top good for 1 <FOOD>.

name: Changeover
desc: At any time, if a field contains exactly 1 good as a result of a harvest, you can discard that good and immediately take a __Sow__ action limited to that field.

name: Bellfounder
desc: In the returning home phase of each round, if you have at least 1 <CLAY>, you can use this card to discard all of your <CLAY> and get your choice of 3 <FOOD> or 1 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Carpenter
desc: Every new room only costs you 3 of the appropriate building resource and 2 <REED> (e.g. if you live in a wooden house, 3 <WOOD> and 2 <REED>).

name: Nave
desc: During scoring, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for each of the 5 columns of your farmyard board containing at least one room.

name: Inner Districts Director
desc: Each time you use the __Forest__ or __Clay Pit__ accumulation space, you can place 1 <STONE> from the general supply on the other space. If you do, you can immediately place another person.

name: Pickler
desc: If there are still 1/3/6/9 complete rounds left to play, you immediately get 1/2/3/4 <WOOD>. During scoring, each player with the most total <VEGETABLE> gets 3 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Lumber Mill
desc: Every improvement costs you 1 <WOOD> less.

name: Recycled Brick
desc: Each time any player (including you) renovates to stone, you get 1 <CLAY> for each newly renovated room.

name: Chimney Sweep
desc: Renovating to stone costs you 2 <STONE> less. During scoring, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for each other player living in a stone house.

name: Sour Dough
desc: Once per round, if all players have at least 1 person left to place, you can skip placing a person and take a __Bake Bread__ action instead.

name: Wholesaler
desc: Place 1 <VEGETABLE>, 1 <PIG>, 1 <STONE>, and 1 <CATTLE> on this card. Each time you use an action space card on round spaces 8 to 11, you get the corresponding good from this card.

name: Butler
desc: If you play this card in round 11 or before, during scoring, you get 4 bonus <SCORE> if you then have more rooms than people.

name: Potter's Yard
desc: Immediately place 1 <CLAY> on each unused space in your farmyard. Each time you turn a space into a used space, you get the clay and you can immediately exchange it for 2 <FOOD>.

name: Sheep Well
desc: Place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next round spaces, up to the number of <SHEEP> you have. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Den Builder
desc: When you live in a clay or stone house, you can pay 1 <GRAIN> and 2 <FOOD>. If you do, for the rest of the game, this card provides room for exactly one person.

name: Master Huntsman
desc: When you play this card and each time you build a major improvement, you get 1 <PIG>.

name: Lumber Virtuoso
desc: Each harvest in which you have at least 5 <WOOD> in your supply, you can discard down to 5 <WOOD> to take a __Build Stables__ or __Build Wood Rooms__ action by paying the usual costs.
